(8 rows)

=> 8 distinct points total. Massive distance ties => same_set/exact_order FALSE (arbitrary tie-break).

### Finding 2 — HARNESS ASSERTION DEFECT (root cause of Part A plan-shape FAIL)
ExplainPlanShape::COMPOSITE_INDEX = 'places_cat_geom' (parent partitioned-index name).
A single-partition scan of 'places' uses the PARTITION-LOCAL child index:
  Index Scan using places_fixture_tier2_category_key_geom_idx  (Index Cond: category_key='airport', Order By: geom <-> ref, 0 recheck, 0 filter-removed, no Sort, no Seq Scan)
The parent name never appears as a scan node => the exact-name match can never pass for partitioned places.

